ReadMe

One if not the easiest way of installing Jenkins server on your linux machine.

Steps below:

1. Download Jenkins-2.176-1.war:
http://repo.jenkins-ci.org/releases/org/jenkins-ci/main/jenkins-war/2.176.1/

2. Set JENKINS_HOME
export JENKINS_HOME=<DIRECTORY WHERE YOU WANT TO PUT JENKINS JOBS OR WORKSPACE>
e.i. JENKINS_HOME=/home/user/jenkins

3.Install Jenkins using war file and specifying port:
$java -jar jenkins-2.176-1.war --httpPort=1961

*note remember or copy temporary password for admin user to be used for first login.

Attached are necessary plugins to support multibranch, *jenkinsfile, pipeline jobs. 
3. After Jenkins server installed. Copy the plugins files *.hpi to .jenkins/plugins directory to enable pipeline, multibranch plugins.
4. Restart Jenkins. sample: do it in the browser. {(jenkins_url)/restart} or http://localhost:8080/restart or http://localhost:1961/restart

Login:
3. http://localhost:1961 or http:xxx.xxx.xxx.xx:xxxx

/end

